description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you looking to expand your skills and enhance your career to include providing Complex Clinical Care or do you already have Complex Care experience?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;Apollo Home Healthcare is seeking experienced Health Care Assistants to support a gentleman with complex care needs. &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;We are looking for dedicated and compassionate Health Care Assistants who are passionate about their job, enjoy delivering one to one support and who can build positive relationships with our service users and their families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our service user has a great sense of humour and would like a like-minded person to join his team who can give and take his banter.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;His hobbies and interests are watching TV especially Football, boxing, UFC and he is a massive Manchester United supporter.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a fantastic opportunity for someone who wants to make a difference to this gentleman’s everyday life.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Experience Required&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* 6 months previous care experience &lt;br /&gt;* Personal Care &lt;br /&gt;* Moving and Handling&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desirable Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* Gastrostomy Care (Peg Feeding)&lt;br /&gt;* Tracheostomy Care &lt;br /&gt;* Spinal Injury Care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We have the following shifts available;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* Day shifts from 8:00am - 8:00pm&lt;br /&gt;* Night shifts from 8:00pm – 8:00am &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;This is a personally rewarding role where you can build on your clinical skills and experience, whilst delivering exceptional care and support to our service user and really making an impact on his day to day life.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Why work for Apollo Home Healthcare?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We specialise in the provision of highly complex clinical care services delivered in the homes of service users.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are passionate about delivering the highest standard of care and we recognise that our Nurses, Healthcare Assistants and Support Workers are integral to doing this. In return for your hard work and dedication you will receive:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible hours to suit&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confirmed rotas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent rates of pay&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Holiday pay&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full clinical training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunity to work with other service users in the area&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ongoing professional training and development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We need key workers on the front line supporting our service users in the fight against the COVID-19 Pandemic.&lt;/p&gt;
